question_title: Will the interest in “laken riley” change between 2026-02-02 and 2026-02-15 according to Google Trends?
summary: Interest in "Laken Riley" is most likely to decrease from Feb 2 to Feb 15, 2026. The Jan 29-31 events (Act anniversary and Ibarra's new trial hearing) likely elevated interest at the start of the window. With no scheduled events until the Feb 22 death anniversary (after resolution), interest should decay. However, the ±3 point threshold makes "Doesn't change" plausible if decay is modest. "Increases" unlikely without unexpected news, as the judge's ruling isn't expected until after March 2.

factors.description: Recent news events (Laken Riley Act anniversary Jan 29 + Ibarra new trial hearing Jan 31) likely elevated interest at start of window
No scheduled events between Feb 2-15 to sustain interest; normal news cycle decay expected
Death anniversary (Feb 22) and judge's ruling (after March 2) both fall AFTER resolution window
±3 point threshold is forgiving; could resolve 'Doesn't change' if decay is modest (~2-3 points)
Low baseline value (14) means limited room to fall; could stay in similar range
Unexpected political mentions or news could spike interest (inherent uncertainty)
